---

<section class="px-4 md:px-16 mb-16 md:mb-[120px]">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-8 items-start">
        <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-4">
            <div class="hard-shadow-sm">
                <img
                    alt="Glenn Dyer, author"
                    class="w-full h-auto grayscale hover:grayscale-0 transition-all duration-700"
                    src="/dad_headshot.jpg"
                />
            </div>
        </div>

        <div
            class="col-span-12 md:col-span-7 md:col-start-6 flex flex-col justify-center pt-4"
        >
            <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
                <div class="w-10 h-0.5 bg-secondary"></div>
                <span
                    class="font-label-caps text-label-caps text-secondary tracking-widest"
                    >AUTHOR</span
                >
            </div>
            <h1
                class="font-headline-xl text-headline-xl text-primary font-bold tracking-tight mb-6"
            >
                Glenn Dyer
            </h1>
            <p
                class="font-label-caps text-label-caps text-on-surface-variant tracking-widest mb-8"
            >
                THE CONOR THORN SERIES
            </p>
            <div class="max-w-2xl space-y-5">
                <p
                    class="font-body-lg text-body-lg text-on-surface-variant leading-relaxed"
                >
                    Glenn Dyer is the author of the Conor Thorn series—five WWII
                    espionage thrillers praised for their meticulous research,
                    breakneck pacing, and authentic period detail. Endorsed by
                    Steve Berry, Jack Carr, and Chris Wallace, his novels have
                    been called "a perfect fit for fans of Alan Furst."
                </p>
                <p
                    class="font-body-md text-body-md text-on-surface-variant leading-relaxed"
                >
                    Each book draws on declassified intelligence records,
                    firsthand wartime accounts, and years of archival
                    research—placing readers at the heart of history's most
                    dangerous secrets.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
